**About Pockit - One.**

Imagine you open Pockit.

The first thing you see is a big, beautiful, colorful wheel. You touch it and gently move your finger until it feels right. That single motion tells Pockit how you’re feeling in this moment.

A little later it asks you a simple question like, “In the last couple of hours, how much energy did you have while working?” You just slide a bar from 0.0 to 1.0.

If you’d rather speak, you tap the big microphone button and talk naturally. You might say, “I had a really good conversation with my team today,” or “I’ve been thinking about changing my morning routine.” Pockit listens and saves what you said.

Over time, it begins to notice patterns in your life. It might share observations like:

“You’ve been rating your energy highest on Tuesday mornings.”

Or: “You mentioned wanting to spend more time on creative work lately.”

You can also talk to it anytime. You can ask, “How have I been feeling about work this month?” or “What have I been saying about my sleep lately?” Pockit remembers everything you’ve told it and gives you honest, calm answers based on your own words and actions.

That’s how Pockit works.

