**Technical Translation:**

**User opens the Pockit app**

Display large interactive Color Wheel on the home screen.

When user touches and drags finger across Color Wheel, capture continuous mood value between 0.0 and 1.0 and store timestamped mood entry.

Present next gentle micro-question to the user.

Display 0.0 to 1.0 precision slider for user response.

Show prominent microphone button labeled “Try it with your voice”.

When user taps microphone button, activate device microphone and stream live audio to backend.

Route audio stream through Silero VAD to remove silence.

Send speech segments to Whisper.cpp for transcription.

Save original audio, transcript, timestamp, and confidence score in database.

Generate embedding using nomic-embed-text-v1.5 at 768 dimensions and store in vector database with metadata.

Run pattern analyzer to identify recurring themes in user’s data.

If relevant pattern is found, generate calm observation and add to user’s insight queue.

Display personalized dashboard showing mood trends, recent observations, and memory summary.

Enable natural language chat interface so user can ask questions about their own history and receive responses based on stored memories.

